<span class="doc-tag">.q2w-header</span>
<h1 class="doc-h1">Header</h1>
<p class="doc-lead">Floating brand bar with logo, title, optional subtitle, and right-aligned action buttons.</p>

<section class="doc-section">
  <h2>Preview</h2>
  <div class="doc-preview" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #eef2f7, #dbe3ec); height: 240px;">
    {% include "previews/header.njk" %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="doc-section">
  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <p>Use this component inside a qgis2web Leaflet export after loading <code>q2w-mapcss.css</code>. Keep generated map JavaScript unchanged unless your workflow needs custom behavior.</p>
  <div class="doc-code">
    <button class="doc-copy">copy</button>
<pre>&lt;div class=&quot;q2w-header&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;q2w-header__brand&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;q2w-header__logo&quot;&gt;q2&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;q2w-header__title&quot;&gt;Map Title&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;q2w-header__sub&quot;&gt;Subtitle&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;q2w-header__actions&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button class=&quot;q2w-btn q2w-btn--icon&quot;&gt;?&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
  </div>
</section>

